Package edu.ncsu.csc216.issue_manager.model.command

Class Command

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.issue_manager.model.command.Command
  • public class Command
extends java.lang.Object
    This class creates objects that encapsulate user actions that can cause the state of a issue to update. Contains two inner enumerations for the possible commands that can cause an issue to update.
    Author:
    symone

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      static class  Command.CommandValue
      An enumeration that represents one of the five possible commands that a user can make for the Issue Manager.
      static class  Command.Resolution
      An enumeration that represents the four possible ways a user can resolve an issue.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Command

        public Command​(Command.CommandValue c,
               java.lang.String ownerId,
               Command.Resolution resolution,
               java.lang.String note)
        Constructor has 4 parameters: CommandValue c, String ownerId, Resolution r, String note Not all parameters are required for each CommandValue. Unneeded values will be passed as null or ignored when the Command is used by the Issue FSM. The following conditions result in an IllegalArgumentException with the message “Invalid information.” when constructing a Command object: A Command with a null CommandValue parameter A Command with a CommandValue of ASSIGN and a null or empty string ownerId. A Command with a CommandValue of RESOLVE and a null resolution. A Command with a null or empty note parameter.
        Parameters:
        ownerId - owner of issue Id
        note - issue note
        c - command value
        resolution - Issue's resolution of type Resolution
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with the message “Invalid information.” when constructing an invalid Command object
